				\begin{document}$$D_\textrm{mac}^\textrm{e} = \frac{\varepsilon _{\textrm{p}}D_\textrm{p}}{\tau }$$\end{document}) is also bound to the bulk diffusivity of the gas.

This model is preferred for modeling diffusion in pore networks that exhibit wide pore size distributions. The commonly used approach of using a single equivalent pore size for the entire macropore network, i.e., applying the Bosanquet equation (Eq. 18) directly using the mean pore width as proposed by Satterfield [39], can result in unrealistically low values for the tortuosity for such materials [34]. This will be discussed further in Sect. 5.3Fig. 3
